This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 4-10, 2012, as National Consumer Protection Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of empowering Americans with clear and concise information to make financial decisions and encourages open and honest competition in the marketplace. It highlights the role of consumer advocacy groups, organizations, and government agencies in promoting consumer protection and educating individuals and families about scams, fraud, and abuse. The article also mentions the efforts of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) in strengthening oversight and accountability in the financial sector and fighting for consumer protections. The "Know Before You Owe" campaign is mentioned as an initiative to simplify home loan applications, student financial aid packages, and credit card agreements. The article concludes by emphasizing the importance of restoring financial security through strong consumer protections and ensuring that no American is left to face unfair practices alone.